OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1776636668
OL,3,C'Face unlock' feature can be tricked
OL,4,Cby photos on 60% of phones, tests show
OL,6,FTesting has revealed that smartphones
OL,7,Ffrom major brands including Samsung
OL,8,Fand Motorola can be unlocked using
OL,9,Fprinted images of the owners face.
OL,11,FConsumer experts have warned that this
OL,12,Fsecurity loophole could be exploited
OL,13,Fby criminals to unlock devices and
OL,14,Faccess personal information.
OL,16,FWhich?, the UK's largest independent
OL,17,Fconsumer organisation, has been
OL,18,Fcarrying out lab tests on hundreds of
OL,19,Fphone models since 2022, assessing
OL,20,Ffeatures from battery life to security
OL,21,Ffeatures.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1776636668
OL,3,C'Face unlock' feature can be tricked
OL,4,Cby photos on 60% of phones, tests show
OL,6,FWhile most smartphones now offer
OL,7,Ffacial recognition to unlock mobile
OL,8,Fdevices, Which?'s testing found that
OL,9,Fas many as 64% of phones - 133 devices
OL,10,Fsince 2022 - could be tricked by a
OL,11,Fprinted image.
OL,13,FPhones that failed the organisation's
OL,14,Ftests include top-of-the-range models
OL,15,Fsuch as the Oppo Find X9 Pro, which
OL,16,Fretails for upwards of #1,000.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
