PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1776636668
OL,3,C'Face unlock' feature can be tricked
OL,4,Cby photos on 60% of phones, tests show
OL,6,FAccording to Which?, Samsung's former
OL,7,Fflagship range of Galaxy S25 phones
OL,8,Fcould all be fooled by a 2D
OL,9,Fphotograph, while the some lower-
OL,10,Fpriced Android phones also struggled,
OL,11,Foften relying on a standard 2D facial
OL,12,Frecognition system.
OL,14,FWhich? Found that the newest Google
OL,15,FPixel models and Samsung Galaxy S26
OL,16,Fseries passed their tests and Apple
OL,17,FFace ID was considerably harder to
OL,18,Ftrick.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1776636668
OL,3,C'Face unlock' feature can be tricked
OL,4,Cby photos on 60% of phones, tests show
OL,6,FThe non-profit says that some device
OL,7,Fcameras take flat pictures, which
OL,8,Fmeans they cannot always distinguish
OL,9,Fbetween a real person and a high-
OL,10,Fresolution photo.
OL,12,FMost phones that failed Which?'s test
OL,13,Fdid have an onscreen message warning
OL,14,Fthat face recognition cannot be relied
OL,15,Fupon for security.
OL,17,FLisa Barber, Which? Tech Editor said:
OL,18,F"These security flaws are far from
OL,19,Fisolated incidents.
OL,26,@zD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
